<br>
1) Allow hide to be pressed while moving.<br>
<br>
This will cure the ridiculous evade problems in high lag and packet loss situations.  It will also allow us to engage sneak/hide if we press hide while already sneaking.  This will bring us back into equality with the current masters of stealth, shadowknights and necros, who all carry and use an easy to get instant-cast non-interruptable invis item that they use to invis themselves as they run.  Rogues can't even do that currently.<br>
<br>
2) Decrease hide reset time.<br>
<br>
10 seconds is much too long to wait for a second evade attempt after a failure, especially if it only drops us one place down on the list (placing us between 2 and 3 means we then become #2 since the current #2 moves to #1.).  Knock it down to 5 second refresh, or even 3.5 second refresh just like Jolt (1.5 second casting time + 2 second refresh time).  Or even have it refresh instantly if you fail.<br>
<br>
<br>
3) As Vaslin suggested in a previous thread:<br>
<br>
<I>>About the sneak/hide programming. How about just making a change to the .ini like [SneakHideZone]=TRUE so that every time you zone into a new area, you're automatically have sneak/hide on?</I><br>
<br>
Can there be a more simple solution to the sneak/hide across zones problem?<br>
<br>
And while you are adding that, you may even accidentally fix the bug where faction is not checked until you are done loading (meanwhile friendly mobs are smashing you to a pulp because they used to hate you long ago).<br>
